  "texts": [
    "This could indicate that the agent has explored all rewarding scenarios or has reached a performance plateau.",
    "At this point, the highest reward achieved and the corresponding state and action are recorded.4.",
    "The environment is then reset for the commencement of the next episode.During evaluation, the use of a moving average on rewards continues to play a crucial role.",
    "It assists in determining when an episode should end due to a lack of improvement, thus ensuring that the evaluation phase efficiently identifies the agent's peak performance.",
    "The highest observed rewards across episodes provide insights into the agent's effectiveness and the robustness of its learning.The next subsection elucidates what our reward function is and how it is calculated."
